The 5 year oil prices have been in January and October:
Jan13 - 112; Oct13 - 110; Jan14 - 106; Oct14 - 90; Jan15 - 47; Oct15 - 49; Jan16 - 31; Oct16 - 51; Jan17 - 56; Oct17 - 57; Jan18 - 68;
This indicates that generally the January price is a reasonable indicator of the October price so we can use the current 68$ mark as a basis for our forecast. As it stands, oil is on a strong upward trajectory and this is set to continue given the extension of OPEC's cut in production ahead of the planned listing of Saudi-owned oil producer Aramco. However, on the other hand, increasing production from non-OPEC countries like the US and Canada could see rises limited. The long-term trend towards electric cars could have some effect as well. Therefore it looks likely that oil prices continue to rise, with a reasonable chance of surpassing $80 though  with significant constraining factors making a levelling off or drop possible.
